intention >

what I’ve learned about intention alignment through CrossFit.
01: your intention is more important than time or reps.
02: if you stay curious about the how, you’re more present in the work.
03: leading with your intention allows you to be exactly who you need to be to feel the progress@ you desire. 
04: when you’re connected to your intention, you rarely want to skip a session.
05: it doesn’t matter when you arrive at your goal as long as you do.
06: rest days aren’t scary or forgotten.
07: you find your team.

I almost didn’t start a career in fitness.

Back in 2013 I finally considered picking up my first official spin class (those who remember the 2006 spin-a-thon remember the real first) and I almost said no.

I didn’t like what I thought the fitness space had become. I was stepping into what felt like a talk no walk, a “look at me” culture.

So I could either not do it (omfg imagine that??!!) or change it.

Come with me has and always will be my motto, my choice to always walk together through life empowering those to join. And finding ways to rise frequency together in a community is truly my soul’s work.

Leaders, we can do better (not more) but we can be better. Better at changing the narrative of what fitness feels like, what inclusivity and community feels like, too.

And I’ll tell you, this vision we brought to life last week was IT. 75 humans who can truly be the change I’ve wanted to see in the fitness space. Still dreaming of this event and a moment that cultivated more of the lets go together rather than against. 

@juliana.jpg @aliciaromanord thanks for walking together to create this — more to come, fam 😏🤩

Overlapping lessons, a love language 📝 

1️⃣ the fear doesn’t go away, you just grow a stronger muscle to lead instead of letting fear decide.

2️⃣ investing (time, money, energy, commitment) will always kind of make you want to 💩 your pants if you’re playing a big game (also read as: imposter syndrome).

3️⃣ it’s a lot harder when you resist resources.  If you’re not resourceful get ready for unnecessary roadblocks. Your willingness to do whatever it takes to find the resources promotes forward progress.

4️⃣ money/weight/anything-number-oriented is not the only way to determine success. Numbers can be both inspiring & wildly misleading so please take them with a grain(or a lot) of salt

5️⃣ your mindset matters. How you show up to any call, workout, meeting, competition matters. And it requires patience, grace, humility. Practice challenging it and staying true to you in the challenge.

and you’re probably reading this exactly when you need it. keep 👏 going 👏

in no particular order… and applicable at any “part” of the process.

1️⃣ growth is 5% knowingness and 95% curiosity: you’re capable of achieving anything you want in this world if you’re willing to commit to being about it, not knowing it all.

2️⃣ your higher self won’t seek validation from others, but your ego and insecurities will: if either are in the drivers seat, you’re out of being.

3️⃣ get messy: and be willing to fail in the mess.

4️⃣ if you’re trying to be someone else, you’re getting further and further away from who you’re meant to be. be inspired, motivated and curious, but don’t forget you’re the only you.

5️⃣ you can either evolve or repeat: repetition isn’t always the most effective if you’re repeating something that keeps you the same. read that again.

yesterday marked 6 whole seasons at my favorite place, @bspokestudios. And what I’ve learned in these 6 years apply more to life than just teaching that I could’ve ever imagined.

✨Trust your intuition. 6 years ago, I knew id be fine stepping into fulltime entrepreneur mode. Did I know how? Nope. Still don’t, enjoy the process and trust the pull. 

🚶‍♀️Not only good instructors, but good people walk the walk — sometimes without even talking the talk. Action always speaks volumes. 

🤩 It actually changes someones life when they feel heard and seen for whoever they are. #comeasyouare

🧲 You attract what you are, remember that. The types of communities you lead are an example of how you’re showing up. You don’t like it? Show up differently. 

🔄 11 years of teaching, and I still crave to be a student. There’s a really beautiful cycle you enter when you’re open to it — student to master, repeat. 

🖤 Love knows no boundaries. And love can actually power an entire journey. 6 years later, nothin but love.

@bspokestudios & @theentirecommunity here’s to the next — I love you forever ♾️

RE|TREAT Mexico, we blew ya out of the water.

A week of holding space, sweat, love, tears with this crew and im feeling some kind of way. There’s something about the strength of these women - hard exterior, go getters, tough loved - and them seeing them soften, release, expand was a whole other thing. 

Honored.
Grateful.
Powerful. 
Proud.
Amongst a lot of other vibes that are currently still loading…

What they dont know is this trip opened up space for me to re|write and re|create my own stories. Something I’m unsure I could ever thank THEM enough for. 

This vision came to me dec 29th (hey @beatrizvb) and seeing it come to reality has completely filled my heart.

Thankful for women who allow themselves to get vulnerable, to be open, to receive love and to share their light. Its incredible what we can create when we just BE.

Until next time (yes there’s another coming)✌️

A medium once told me I’m the vehicle for my dad to continue to grow, evolve and change the world.

tbh, a thought I’ll always close.

I can’t help but think about this journey we refer to as our life — knowing that those we “lose” now have the best seat in the house at witnessing what they’ve passed along to us. It’s quite beautiful to actually see-through the veil of “real” and get more and more curious about how these two worlds collide; how it’s us that actually keep spirits alive. (👋🏼 @veronicamarie___ )

It’s simple, they exist where we carry them. And it’s us who have the honor to pass them down. So while it’s been almost 15 (!!) birthdays since my dad’s been on the earth, his birthday was still very much so celebrated and remembered yesterday. 

For those of you missing someone on their birthday, create a way to celebrate. Write a birthday card, sing, tell stories… and also remember that’s not the only day their spirit exists.

#hbd #grief #griefjourney #teammooch #strikeoutals #alsawareness

“How do you know when it’s time?”

I spent most of my life having NO clue if it was the “right time” more with the right feeling. If you ask my mom, I was always the risk-taker, the slightly impulsive, imma-just-close-my-eyes-and-jump type soul. 

Usually I would jump before I knew what was going to happen. It was like I just trusted myself to make it work. 

I’ve felt this wave of “jumping” for some time now. Like when you’re watching a scary movie and just waiting for the fake looking monster to pop out. You know it’s coming, you can hear the change in dramatic music, and then it happens. It’s time.

Jumping = you better learn to fly, girl.

Jumping = change.

Change can:
Be hard (af)
Be Scary
Cause frustration and angst
Feel unsettling 
Make you pee your pants (anyone else?)
Question things
Even question yourself 

And change can also:
Empower you
Push you out of your comfort zone
Inspire you
Motivate gratitude
Level you the f*ck up. 

I’ll choose the latter every day.

So yes as i quite literally lay on the floor, coworking on a sunday with my sis @veronicamarie___ (and a side of trader joe’s snacks), that’s what got me thinking about another jump 👀 

Lets go get it, kids.

out of your head 💭 and back into your heart 🫀

for me, travel always sheds new light on perspective. in a conversation with a friend in Austin last week week I was reminded the disruption thinking (and overthinking) has on feeling.

to feel more:
✨ be the observer of your feels versus changing them
✨ be light with your thoughts 
✨ meditate then journal
✨ try something outside of your routine 
✨ respect your nervous system - slow down
✨ practice gratitude - not just for everything else but gratitude for yourself

a reminder for you this week, get in your feels and stay there. Let them be your guide 🪄
